## Data Flow — Init to Animate

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant U as User
    participant C as card.js
    participant T as Three.js
    participant L as TextureLoader
    participant A as Animation loop

    U->>C: Card loads on canvas
    C->>C: Create scene, camera, renderer
    C->>C: Add OrbitControls
    C->>C: Create Sun mesh (emissive)
    C->>C: Create 8 planet meshes
    C->>C: Create Saturn ring geometry
    C->>C: Create orbital path lines
    C->>C: Create starfield points
    C->>C: Create HTML labels + info panel

    C->>L: Load textures (parallel)
    L-->>C: Textures loaded or fallback
    C->>T: Append scene to container
    C->>T: Set up resize handler

    loop every frame
        A->>C: requestAnimationFrame
        C->>A: Update orbital positions<br/>Kepler's law: omega = 2*PI/T
        C->>A: Rotate planets on axis
        C->>T: Render scene
        C->>C: Update label positions
    end

    U->>C: User zooms / pans / rotates
    C->>C: OrbitControls handles input
    C->>T: Re-render with new camera
```

## Planet Data Model

```mermaid
classDiagram
    class PlanetConfig {
        +string name
        +float distance
        +float period
        +float size
        +float tilt
        +float speed
        +string textureUrl
        +string color
    }

    class Planet {
        +Mesh mesh
        +Group group
        +float phase
        +float angle
        +update(time)
        +rotate()
        +dispose()
    }

    class SaturnRings {
        +Mesh ringMesh
        +RingGeometry geometry
        +update()
        +dispose()
    }

    class Starfield {
        +Points points
        +BufferGeometry geometry
        +createStars(count)
        +dispose()
    }

    class InfoPanel {
        +HTMLElement container
        +showPlanet(name, info)
        +hide()
    }

    PlanetConfig --> Planet : configures
    Planet *-- SaturnRings
    PlanetConfig : 8 instances --> Planet
```

